		{"id":"0bc219f40019f390","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/Things taking all her Spoons.md","x":4255,"y":1480,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"8f072582c87a2d00","type":"text","text":"As far as the wolf's perspective, I mean it likes all things shaped like the moon, so it already likes the necklace as soon as it sees it, and thanks to the hug and stuff from her mother it has established that these are pack members, and then later she charges the Crystal and puts it on and gets that effect of being able to communicate with the wolf better, so that's going to really shift things with the wolf. Coming from this sort of negative place of it chafing at being drained all the time, to not being drained and so therefore neutral sort of place, to I guess you could say feeling more supported? Like it's learning that it can trust her I guess, I don't want it to have too much of a long-term thing. Like it doesn't hold grudges, because I don't feel like that's how dogs operate. Not that it can't ever remember anything, but it doesn't continue to throw tantrums and be pissy because it was being drained previously even after it's stopped being drained. I don't know I just feel like my dog usually is just reacting to the situation at hand without having too much of the past or future influencing her mood and stuff, so I want the inner wolf to be like that. I mean maybe it to some degree the werewolf didn't know why it felt bad, it was brand new maybe it was just simply too young to really understand that it was being drained by the fairy just that it didn't feel good and it's needs weren't being met. So that it doesn't really establish a learned association. But anyway, I think the wolf coming into this place where it feels like it can trust her is at least a foundation towards it letting her have control when they are in wolf form. I think I like that idea, it takes control when it feels like it can't trust her. It's just it can only take control while there and we'll form, at least like major control. Not that it can't make her growl or something in human form, but it's easier for the wolf to have control over the actions when they are in wolf form but her consistently meeting its needs and the necklace helping with communication so that she can understand it and what it means like I said is going to establish this sort of trust, the wolf feels safe letting her metaphorically drive when she embraces the wolf and takes care of the wolf. ","x":3213,"y":1530,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"347d35ff5848fcca","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/MoonPetal Nectar.md","x":4255,"y":3640,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"e2aa09e08406d7ae","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/Moonpetal Punch effects notes.md","x":3790,"y":3640,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"569b81f5c5c05a1f","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/Moonstone delivery.md","x":6320,"y":3880,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"d75c69f23788a290","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/Transform 2.md","x":5185,"y":-211,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"ef428fefc6292227","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/Don checks on Sara.md","x":5650,"y":-211,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"71482cf22b6c1893","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/Moonpetal Harvesting.md","x":4255,"y":2360,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"3d020125b954c117","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/First full moon.md","x":3790,"y":2360,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"c342900f6fe36250","type":"text","text":"I could have Sara and Cass all sitting out in the outdoor \"living room\" that's some folding chairs. Maybe Sara does have a bandage, just the one. And she's like \"Oh this? It's nothing, really. I'm fine.\" \n\nPart of Emma wanted to point out that she would heal better if she got out of the sun, but Cass already looked uncomfortable about it. And had her own bandage. Strange indeed. So she left it alone, for now. \"I was hoping to talk to Jane. Is she about somewhere?\"\n\n\"I think, oh, there she is.\" Sara pointed. \n\nEmma turned and saw Jane come flying into view. On fairy wings. Emma frowned, was her family allergic to staying human or something? Not that she had room to talk, but still. Even Cass's life energy was different somehow. \n\n\"Grandma can fly?\" Ben asked, eyes lit with wonder. \n\nSara cocked an eye brow at Emma. \"Grandma?\" \n\nEmma sighed, and rubbed her eyes while she waited for Jane to come closer. She didn't want to have to repeat this. It was going to be hard enough to say it once. \n\nJane landed, \"Emma! And who do we have here?\" she smiled. \n\n\"This is Ben and Grant... Savanna's boys.\" \n\nEveryone sort of paused, except Grant. \n\n\"Kinda...\" Grant rubbed his neck, probably better to be honest. \"Technically Savanna was my grandmother.\" \n\nBen looked sad, \"She was our mother.\" \n\nGrant gave him a hug. \"I know buddy.\" \n\nSara looked to Emma and mouthed \"Was?\"\n\nEmma nodded and mouthed back, \"She's gone. Like gone gone.\" \n\nJane bit her lip. Cass looked down. \n\nSara stood. \"I need a minute.\" She walked off into the trees. \n\nCass stood and turned toward where she had gone. \n\n\"Let her go Cass.\" Jane sighed. \"She'll need space.\" \n\n\"But...\"\n\n\"Trust me, she'll come to us when she's ready.\" \n\n\"Are we gonna be in trouble?\" Ben asked. \"Since we made her mad.\"\n\n\"You didn't make her mad, sweetie.\" Jane shook her head. \"Your grandma Sara is hurt; she always thought Savanna would come back to us some day.\" ","x":7280,"y":-1618,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"9ce7058d1f5a5679","type":"text","text":"Emma is on the job one day, when she realizes she's reaping Savanna's soul. Once it's gone, Emma is spotted by two boys, a teen and a child. The child spoke first, \"Mom? Is that you?\"\n\n\"She's not...\" The older one started, but sounded so unsure. \"Who are you? Why do you look like Savanna?\"\n\nEmma was gonna... give grim a piece of her mind. She couldn't actually do anything to death, but he had to have known. Just like he'd known about Brenda, he had known exactly what he was sending her into. \"You're better off not knowing.\" Emma turned to leave. \n\n\"Mom, wait, don't go!\" Ben teared up instantly. \n\nEmma was frozen with grief. How she wanted to hear those words, but from someone else.\n\nGrant got serious. \"That is not an answer. Why do you look like Savanna? Is this death's idea of a cruel joke, to appear like the person you're here for?\"\n\nEmma eyes watered. \"Savanna was my twin sister.\" \n\n\"Twin?\" Grant back and forth from Savanna to the woman in the black cloak. \"You're our aunt?\" Well, great aunt for him, but that didn't make her not family to him. \"Then please, take us with you.\" \n\nEmma shook her head. \"Your father can take care of you.\"\n\n\"Is Daddy come back then?\" Ben sounded so hurt. \n\nGrant swallowed. \"No Ben, he can't.\"\n\n\"I can help you find him.\" Emma offered. \n\n\"Genji is dead. Please take us with you.\" Grant tried again. \n\n\"Yeah, I wanna live with you.\" Ben sniffled. \n\n\"Boys, I'm the reason your mother left, you want no part of this.\" Savanna had hated all of them, but she had hated Emma the most. She would have never wanted her children to live with Emma. Plus Emma couldn't stand the idea of having someone else leave. \n\n\"If you leave us here, what are we supposed to do? Savanna could barely make the rent here, what makes you think I can get a job to cover that and groceries?\"\n\nIt was such a practical question. This teen knew how the world worked, at least on some level. Emma supposed she shouldn't have surprised her, the kid had Jane's unique eye color, just like Emma herself did. They were family, she couldn't just leave them. And speaking of Jane, Emma was willing to bet her mother would take in two more human kids. \"Alright, I know someone, I'll take you to them.\"\n\n\"Who?\" The teen hesitated. \n\n\"My mother, your grandmother: Jane. But first, what are your names?\" ","x":6760,"y":-1618,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"1e4f5f3f20aea244","x":7780,"y":-1618,"width":400,"height":400,"type":"text","text":"Grant looked towards where Sara had gone. He would bet that hurt was why Emma had hesitated to come here. Would they truly be welcome here? \n\nCass turned to Jane and held her middle, \"Hey, um,\" her stomach growled loudly and she tensed. \n\nJane turned to the boys, \"In the mean time, when was the last time you boys ate? I bet you're hungry.\" She stood. \"I think I'll make some sausage, popcorn, and what do you boys like?\"\n\n\"I wanna come help make popcorn!\" Ben beamed and went over to her. \n\nGrant found himself smiling a little, Ben always loved it when they made popcorn. \n\n\"Alright, extra popcorn!\" Jane matched Ben's big grin. \"What about you, Grant?\"\n\nHe shrugged, \"Anything is fine really, I'm not picky.\" \n\n\"Ok, as long as you're sure. You going to be ok Cass?\" \n\n\"Yeah, I'm good for now.\" She closed the cooler next to her and held up a bag of jerky. \n\n\"Alright then,\" Jane offered Ben her hand, \"Popcorn making time!\" "},
		{"id":"e465deecb857c43a","type":"file","file":"Sims4-Yootz-Story/plans/spoilers/After Full Moon Notes.md","x":8820,"y":-880,"width":820,"height":460},
		{"id":"86c17cb984d99dd3","x":9520,"y":-1618,"width":400,"height":400,"type":"text","text":"Grant took a bite of the popcorn. It tasted just like when he made it the way he had watched Savanna make it. All of it was the same: the butter, the sugar, all the seasonings, everything was just right. The realization hit him all at once: it was never Savanna's recipe, it was Jane's all along. \n\nHe smiled up at Jane, \"Thank you, it's great.\" "},
		{"id":"b10a43089fa67e62","x":8920,"y":-1618,"width":400,"height":400,"type":"text","text":"Grant can notice Cass rubbing her moonstone necklace"},
		{"id":"e606fcacf119c8e0","type":"text","text":"Once Ben and Jane were out of earshot, Emma came in close to Grant, \"So Ben is your...?\" Emma let the question hang.\n\n\"Technically, he's my uncle.\" Grant kept his voice low. \"He doesn't remember my mom. Well, neither of us really do. I was really young when it happened, and he was just a newborn. He doesn't really know he had an older sister, he just sees me as his brother.\" \n\nEmma had almost left this kid to raise his younger uncle? She was definitely glad she had brought them here. \"And Genji was...?\" \n\n\"Ben's dad, and my grandad.\" Again Grant figured being honest was probably for the best. The truth was complicated enough without adding any lies. \"My dad isn't dead, he's just... married with a family of his own. I doubt he would take me in, and even if he did, there is no way they would take in the brother of... I think 'the homewrecker' was what his wife called my mom? So that wasn't an option.\" \n\nEmma found it interesting, technically Grant might have had an out, but she wasn't even sure he saw it because he was so protective of Ben. Not that she didn't understand that protective nature, it had been impossible not to notice it in herself. There was no denying it, he was one of them. \"You're going to fit in just fine here kid.\" Emma went back to her chair and just relaxed as she sighed. She had missed everyone. While her need to phase to a ghost was there, she didn't want to leave. She also needed to be here, to be with her family. She could stay solid for a while longer. ","x":8320,"y":-1618,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"14a5387998910ec7","type":"text","text":"They arrived together at Gibbi point. Emma sighed. She could feel her soul trying to assert itself again. The need to phase into a ghost was raising, so she needed to make this quick. \n\nEmma came up to the cabin door and knocked. \"Mom?\" She called. \n\nBut it was Sara who opened the door. Covered in bandages. \"Hey Emma sweetie, what brings...\" she sounded so tired.  \n\n\"Mom? What happened to you?\" \n\nHer sigh was more tired than her voice. \"It's a long story. But first come in dear.\"\n\n\"You want some tea or something?\" Don asked from over on the couch. He was covered in bandages too. \n\n\"No, that's ok. I wasn't planning to stay long, where's Jane?\" Emma stepped inside. \"Come on in boys.\" \n\nI'm thinking like maybe this is the morning after the full moon? \n\n\"She should be back soon. But first, who do we have here?\" \n\nWhen? \n\nSo I'm looking at when this all happens. It can't be right after the full moon. Jane wouldn't leave Cass at that point. \n\nI do like Sara opening the door but idk if it makes sense.\n\nso that Emma is like mom what are you doing out in the sun. Well, though Emma would know Sara can be out in the sun for a bit. ","x":7280,"y":-2580,"width":400,"height":400},
		{"id":"e25ce00d0c122f10","x":6760,"y":-2580,"width":400,"height":400,"type":"text","text":"Emma tries to convince them they're better off, to not follow her. Emma knows her sister would have never wanted them with her, with any of the family. She's also hurt about how her sister left and hated her, and she's still grieving the sort of happy sad that is Brenda. She likes that her daughter is safe, but that doesn't mean she doesn't miss her. "}
	],
